OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Tue 21 Jul to Thu 30 Jul
OL,6,FInitially predominantly dry with large
OL,7,Fsunny spells away from the northwest
OL,8,Fwhere cooler, cloudier and wetter
OL,9,Fconditions are most likely. Though
OL,10,Fthere will be a few isolated showers
OL,11,Ffurther south at times. Becoming very
OL,12,Fwarm again in parts of the south
OL,13,Fbefore the weekend introduces a more
OL,14,Fwidely unsettled and showery period
OL,15,Fincluding risk of thunderstorms -
OL,16,Fthough still some good sunny spells
OL,17,Fand temperatures around or just above
OL,18,Faverage for most. Toward the end of
OL,19,Fthe month uncertainty increases, but
OL,20,Fpotentially returning to a drier,
OL,21,Fsettled and warm period, in the south
OL,22,Fespecially.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
